The sampler controls how the next token is chosen from a set of probable choices.
Min-P: Rejects low-probability tokens in favor of more coherent output with higher word diversity, even at higher temperatures. (Default) Top-K: Limits sample to the k-highest probability tokens from the set of most probable tokens with cumulative probability less than p.
